@kumarnikhil936 As @bennyooo noted, support for Keras is not available in 1.9. Please use the nightly build. You can do that by either using "pip install --upgrade tf_nightly" or follow the instructions here.

@bennyooo Can you provide your Keras model file and the set of commands (or code) you used to convert your model?

@kumarnikhil936 As @bennyooo noted, support for Keras is not available in 1.9. Please use the nightly build. You can do that by either using "pip install --upgrade tf_nightly" or follow the instructions [here](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_sources).
